The paper deals with list decoding of Gabidulin codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves subspace properties, which are related to coding theory and algebraic geometry, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the Johnson radius, which is a concept in coding theory and combinatorics, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and proofs, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
